<script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">
$('input[name="field74"], input[name="dob"]').change( function()
{
d1 = $('input[name="dob"]').datepicker('getDate');
d2 = $('input[name="field74"]').datepicker('getDate');
function calcDate(d1,d2) {
var diff = Math.floor(d2.getTime() - d1.getTime());

var years = Math.floor(diff/31536000000);
var months= Math.floor((diff%31536000000)/2628000000);
var days = Math.floor(((diff%31536000000)%2628000000)/86400000);
 var msg  = years + " years ";
     msg += months + " months ";
     msg += days + " days " ;

return msg
}
a = calcDate(d1,d2)
$('input[name=days]').val(a);
});
</script>
